stories: Innovative spectrograms represent patterns in audio signals of neural networks, whose interpretation and property analysis are vital indicators for cognitive processing. Nevertheless, challenges associated with noise and variability of data as well as the complexity of cognitive phenomena of interest have hindered an automatic and bespoke analysis framework, often still relying (in part) on human annotation and verification. We introduce a feature extraction framework for spectrograms, built from unsupervised, clustering-based machine learning methods, which facilitates the direct identification and quantification of cognitive properties of the former. thereby, the need for human input or large training datasets to inform supervised learning approaches is circumvented, while additionally enabling the automation of pixelwise shape and feature labeling. In particular, we demonstrate that auditory attention detection can be conducted effectively, efficiently and without any training data as a direct result of this approach.

Innovative topological maps represent patterns in spatial data of complex systems, whose interpretation and property analysis are vital indicators for environmental sustainability. Nevertheless, challenges associated with noise and variability of data as well as the complexity of ecological phenomena of interest have hindered an automatic and bespoke analysis framework, often still relying (in part) on human observation and verification. We introduce a feature extraction framework for topological maps, built from unsupervised, clustering-based machine learning methods, which facilitates the direct identification and quantification of ecological properties of the former. thereby, the need for human input or large training datasets to inform supervised learning approaches is circumvented, while additionally enabling the automation of pixelwise shape and feature labeling. In particular, we demonstrate that land use classification can be conducted effectively, efficiently and without any training data as a direct result of this approach.
